The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Thursday, July 15, 2004 				 Farmer suicides
Yavatmal/Nagpur, July 14 (PTI): Frustrated by the damage to their crop due to delayed monsoon and mounting debt, seven farmers in Vidarbha region of Maharashtra allegedly committed suicide in one week, taking the number of such deaths in the region to 21.																								In Pusad taluka of Yavatmal district, a farmer holding three acres of land allegedly committed suicide yesterday. His soya crop, for which he had taken loan from a cooperative society, was damaged due to inadequate rainfall, reports said today.																								Another farmer from Narkhed taluka in rural Nagpur ended his life two days ago by consuming insecticides.																								A farmer each in villages in Pandharkawada tehsil, Zatala, Yelabara, Padha and Wadhona Bazaar also committed suicide last week owing to the burden of resowing and repayment of crop loan, the reports added.																								Farmers in Babhulgaon tehsil, however, ended their indefinite hunger strike after district guardian minister Vasantrao Purke assured them that the government would provide them relief.
